Training sentences {example sentences (Walker et al., 1994) (43 sentences), a folk tale Kobutori jiisan (Nakao, 1985) (93 sentences), an essay in Tenseijingo (26 sentences), an editorial (26 sentences)} Test sentences {a folk tale Tsuru no ongaeshi (Nakao, 1985) (91 sentences), two essays in Tenseijingo (50 sentences), an editorial (30 sentences)} Precision is the fraction of the noun phrases which were judged to have the indirect anaphora as antecedents.
